'''Hendrik''' "'''Hent'''" '''de Vries''' (born 24 February 1958,<ref name=Congress>{{cite web |title= Vries, Hent de |url= http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n89643830.html |publisher= Library of Congress |accessdate= 22 July 2014 |quote= (b. 2/24/58) }}type=simple;lang=en;c=ap;rgn1=entirerecord;q1=Vries;x=9;y=11;cc=ap;view=reslist;sort=achternaam;fmt=long;page=reslist;size=1;start=195 Prof. dr. H. de Vries, 1958 -] at the [[University of Amsterdam]] ''Album Academicum'' website</ref> is a Dutch philosopher, Professor of the Humanities and Philosophy at the [[Johns Hopkins University]], and Professor of Philosophy at the [[University of Amsterdam]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://humctr.jhu.edu/bios/hent-devries |title=Johns Hopkins University: Faculty Bio |accessdate= |format= |work= }}</ref> De Vries has been instrumental in explaining the apophatic and other theological claims and dimensions of deconstruction and for demonstrating its import for an understanding of religion in contemporary philosophy and culture.
