{{korean name|[[Heo (Korean name)|Heo]]}} {{unreferenced|date=March 2012}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}
'''Heo Jeok''' (1610 – May 11, 1680) was a politician during the [[Joseon Dynasty]]. He was the 124th and 125th Prime Minister of Korea ([[Yeonguijeong]]), in 1664, 1671, and 1674–1680. His [[pen name]] was Mukjae, Hyuong.
He was the leader of the [[Southerners (Korean political faction)|Southerners faction]], and a rival of [[Song Siyeol]].
== Works == * Ilgi (일기, 日記) * Heosanggukjooui (허상국주의, 許相國奏議)
== See also == * [[Yesong]] * [[Heo Mok]] * [[Yun Hyu]] * [[Yun Seondo]]
