'''Hong Uwon''' ([[Korea]]n:홍우원, [[hanja]]:洪宇遠, July 29, 1605 - July 27, 1687) was one of the [[Neo-Confucian]] scholars, politicians and writers of the [[Korea]]n [[Joseon Dynasty]]. His nickname was '''Nampa'''(남파, 南坡), a [[courtesy name]] was Gunjing(군징, 君徵).
