{{About|the philosopher|the cinematographer|Peter Menzies Jr.}}

'''Peter Menzies''' (5 Feb 1953 - 6 Feb 2015) was an Australian [[philosophy|philosopher]] and past president of the [[Australasian Association of Philosophy]], who held teaching positions at [[Macquarie University]], [[University of Sydney]], and [[Australian National University]].<ref name='obit'>{{cite web|title = Professor Peter Menzies| publisher = Australasian Association of Philosophy| url =  https://aap.org.au/blog/3226205 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160801042454/https://aap.org.au/blog/3226205 | archivedate = 1 Aug 2016 | accessdate = 21 Dec 2017}}</ref>  He specialized in [[metaphysics]], especially the [[Causality|philosophy of causation]].<ref name="MenPrice">{{cite journal | last1 = Menzies | first1 = P. | last2 = Price | first2 = H. | year = 1993 | title = Causation as a Secondary Quality | url = | journal = British Journal for the Philosophy of Science | volume = 44 | issue = | pages = 187–203 | doi=10.1093/bjps/44.2.187}}</ref><ref name='ajp-obit'>{{cite journal | last = Price | first = Huw | title = Obituary, Peter Menzies (1953 - 2015) | journal = Australasian Journal of Philosophy | volume = 93 | issue =2 | date = 2015}}</ref> He became a fellow of the [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]] in 2007.<ref name='obit'/>

Menzies was a student of [[Nancy Cartwright (philosopher)|Nancy Cartwright]] at [[Stanford University]] where he received his PhD in 1984.<ref name='cv'>{{cite web | title = Peter Menzies CV | url = https://www.mq.edu.au/pubstatic/public/download.jsp?id=63536 | accessdate = 21 Dec 2017}}</ref>

He and philosopher [[Huw Price]] developed a version of [[Agent causation|Agency Theory of Causation]], which is statement of manipulability theory of causation.  In this view, human actors play an important role in cause and effect.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |last1=Woodward |first1=James |title= Causation and Manipulability |url= https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/win2016/entries/causation-mani/ |encyclopedia= Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy (Winter 2016 Edition) | access-date= 21 Dec 2017}}</ref>

